WEBVTT

00:04.221 --> 00:06.440
[ Man ] One, two. One, two, three.

00:38.167 --> 00:41.301
Yes. Good thing I noticed
the similar shapes.

00:41.432 --> 00:46.350
[ Hermes ] Planet Express stockholders, I present our Chief Executive Officer,

00:46.481 --> 00:49.744
Professor Hubert Farnsworth!Oh?

00:49.875 --> 00:53.530
[ Cheering ]There he is!
Take it off!

00:53.661 --> 00:58.274
W-Where am I?Move forward!
Walk into the light!

00:58.405 --> 01:00.756
Oh, God! I'm dead!

01:00.886 --> 01:03.715
Well, no matter.

01:03.846 --> 01:07.545
Thank you all for coming.
I don't recognize any of you,

01:07.676 --> 01:10.243
nor can I recall
why I am here.

01:10.373 --> 01:12.245
Now, without further ado,

01:12.376 --> 01:15.031
a film highlighting
Planet Express, Inc.'s...

01:15.162 --> 01:17.293
latest fiscal year.[ Applause ]

01:17.424 --> 01:21.429
[ Man Narrating ]
Planet Express is on the move!

01:21.558 --> 01:23.822
For this hip,
young delivery company,

01:23.953 --> 01:28.000
tomorrow is today,
and today is yesterday.

01:28.131 --> 01:30.176
You heard me.

01:31.394 --> 01:33.310
It was a year
of soaring profits...

01:33.441 --> 01:36.747
and significant
one-time losses.

01:39.402 --> 01:41.448
Psst! Watching myself work
is making me hungry.

01:41.579 --> 01:43.537
Help me find
some food somewhere.

01:43.668 --> 01:46.801
I'll not only help you find it,
I'll help you do more to it.

01:46.932 --> 01:49.543
[ Keyboard
Clacking ][ Giggles ]

01:49.674 --> 01:52.590
Ooh, a bot-mitzvah!
Shalom hunger.

01:52.721 --> 01:55.593
Shalom free food.

01:55.723 --> 01:59.814
No shellfish![ High-pitched Yelp ]
That is so unfair.

01:59.944 --> 02:01.990
[ Snort ]
Tell me about it.

02:02.121 --> 02:04.210
♪♪ [ Klezmer ] [ Partyers Chattering ]

02:12.393 --> 02:15.264
So, what's the deal?
You guys don't believe
in Robot-Jesus?

02:15.396 --> 02:18.181
We believe he was built,
and that he was a very
well-programmed robot.

02:18.312 --> 02:20.182
But he wasn't
our Messiah.

02:21.793 --> 02:24.579
[ Narrator ]
And so our company
flames onwards.

02:24.709 --> 02:28.670
Planet Express!
Limitless potential,
boundless horizons!

02:28.800 --> 02:32.586
The unstoppable juggernaut
of the corporate universe!

02:32.716 --> 02:35.676
It's been a terrible year,
people.

02:35.807 --> 02:37.808
The company is on the verge
of bankruptcy.

02:37.939 --> 02:40.247
[ Collective Gasp ]Oh, no.
But the movie--

02:40.377 --> 02:43.250
Was a substantial loss
for the company.[ Pointer Beeps ]

02:43.379 --> 02:47.167
The blue pie slice represents
the money we earned
from shipping packages,

02:47.296 --> 02:51.823
while the green slice
represents an $8.00 bank error
in our favor.

02:51.954 --> 02:54.043
This toads the wet sprocket.

02:54.174 --> 02:56.479
- What about our thousands
of shares of stock?
- Worthless.

02:56.610 --> 03:00.831
I'll kill you!I own one share
of Planet Kajigger,

03:00.962 --> 03:03.182
so I'm entitled
to some answers.

03:03.312 --> 03:06.707
Question one:
Why does no one visit me
in my home?

03:06.837 --> 03:10.538
'Cause your apartment smells
like Poly Grip and cat pee!

03:10.668 --> 03:14.542
[ Fry Gasps ] This is perfect for me!

03:17.197 --> 03:20.896
Question. Do you have
to have been cryogenically
frozen to get the free--

03:21.026 --> 03:23.420
[ Groans ]
You didn't let me finish!

03:23.550 --> 03:25.943
I was going to say
"to get the free food!"

03:26.074 --> 03:28.729
[ Voracious Munching ]

03:28.860 --> 03:33.168
My name's Joe,
and I'm a defrostee.[ Group ] Hello, Joe.

03:33.300 --> 03:36.389
When I was frozen,
giant carrots ruled the Earth.

03:36.520 --> 03:39.305
But now they don't.
It takes some getting used to.

03:41.917 --> 03:45.007
Back in the 1980s,
I was the toast
of Wall Street.

03:45.137 --> 03:48.444
I was havin'
whiskey with Boesky
and cookies with Milken.

03:48.575 --> 03:52.449
But then,
I was diagnosed with
terminal bone-itis.

03:52.579 --> 03:54.450
Bone-itis?
[ Sputtering Laugh ]

03:54.581 --> 03:56.365
That's a funny name
for a horrible disease.

03:56.497 --> 03:58.324
There was no cure
at the time.

03:58.454 --> 04:00.805
One drug company was close,
but I arranged...

04:00.936 --> 04:03.330
a hostile takeover
and sold off all the assets.

04:03.460 --> 04:07.377
Made a cool hundred mil.
[ Laughs, Coughs ]

04:11.425 --> 04:14.122
Naturally, I froze myself
until a cure was found.

04:14.253 --> 04:17.343
And now here I am,
ready to sleaze my way
back to the top...

04:17.473 --> 04:19.562
'80s-style.

04:21.348 --> 04:25.307
As a caveman
frozen in a glacier,
I faced different challenges.

04:25.439 --> 04:29.442
The hardest thing
was seeing my wife on display
in the British Museum.

04:29.572 --> 04:31.619
[ Sympathetic Murmurs ]

04:31.749 --> 04:34.012
Hey, buddy,
I'm from the same time as you.

04:34.143 --> 04:36.579
Remember that song,
"Safety Dance"?Sure do.

04:36.711 --> 04:38.625
♪ We can dance
Dun-dun, dun-dun ♪

04:38.755 --> 04:41.149
♪ Dun-dun-dun, dun-dun
Dun-dun, dun-dun, dun-- ♪♪

04:41.281 --> 04:43.805
[ Both Laugh ]

04:43.935 --> 04:46.197
You know, that dance wasn't
as safe as they said it was.

04:46.329 --> 04:49.331
I tell ya, two go-go
'80s Reaganauts like us,

04:49.463 --> 04:51.987
- we could rule this world!
- No question.

04:52.117 --> 04:54.511
If only someone
would give us a shot.

04:54.641 --> 04:57.557
They're scared of our raw power.
Oh, but if you want a job,

04:57.687 --> 04:59.776
I could beg everyone
at the company where I work.

04:59.908 --> 05:03.519
Awesome.
Awesome to the max!

05:03.651 --> 05:08.350
And finally,
the post office meter
is for business mail only.

05:08.481 --> 05:12.268
Ah, come on! I've got a lot
of ransom notes to send!

05:12.399 --> 05:14.836
Enough talk!
It's time for action!

05:14.966 --> 05:19.230
I move that everyone
come to my apartment
to snuggle my cat.

05:19.362 --> 05:22.670
- Second.
- I move that your cat
stinks and is ugly.

05:22.800 --> 05:25.237
- Second.
- I move that we vote on...

05:25.367 --> 05:28.327
a new chief executive officer
and oust this old creep!

05:28.457 --> 05:31.026
And also that my cat
smells good and is pretty.

05:31.156 --> 05:32.766
Second.

05:32.896 --> 05:35.682
Very well.
I nominate the professor!

05:35.812 --> 05:37.858
Second.
Second.
Second.
I'm your man!

05:37.988 --> 05:40.427
I vote my 10,000 shares
for the professor.

05:40.557 --> 05:42.428
Yeah, the professor!Me too!
Me?

05:45.040 --> 05:47.564
I nominate that guy!
Not just because he has a suit,

05:47.694 --> 05:50.350
but because he knows
about business and stuff,
and he has a tie.

05:50.480 --> 05:52.351
[ All Murmuring ]

05:52.481 --> 05:55.223
My shares still count
if they went through
the washing machine, right?

05:57.225 --> 06:01.360
Well, if I know anything about
which number is bigger than
the other number, I'd say--

06:01.490 --> 06:05.930
Now, hold on there.
Scruffy votes his 40,000 shares
for the mysterious stranger.

06:06.060 --> 06:10.586
Forty thousand? How come
you have four times as much
stock as the rest of us?

06:10.718 --> 06:14.156
Scruffy believes
in this company.
[ Sniffles ]

06:14.286 --> 06:17.942
Then we have a tie,
and in the event of a tie...

06:18.072 --> 06:20.814
the professor,
as current C.E.O.,
remains--

06:20.944 --> 06:24.471
I demand the floor!
I may only have one share,

06:24.600 --> 06:26.646
but I get to vote,
same as anyone.

06:26.776 --> 06:29.040
And I'm voting
against the cat hater!

06:29.170 --> 06:31.608
Isn't that right,
kitty?[ Meows ]

06:31.738 --> 06:35.350
Hey!
You ate my change![ Cat Jingling ]

06:36.526 --> 06:39.659
Then it's settled. The new
chief executive officer...

06:39.790 --> 06:41.749
of Planet Express
Corporation is...

06:41.879 --> 06:43.750
That Guy!

06:43.880 --> 06:47.494
♪ Dun-dun, dun-dun,
dun-dun-dun, dun-dun, dun-dun,
dun-dun, dun-dun-dun, dun-- ♪

06:52.411 --> 06:56.459
Please welcome our new
Chief Executive Officer,
That Guy!

06:57.547 --> 07:00.637
Yay!
Whoo-whoo-whoo!

07:00.767 --> 07:04.946
Let's cut to the chase.
There are two kinds of people,
sheep and sharks.

07:05.076 --> 07:07.077
Anyone who's a sheep
is fired.

07:07.209 --> 07:10.168
Who's a sheep? Uh, excuse me.

07:10.298 --> 07:12.170
Which is the one
people like to hug?

07:12.300 --> 07:14.476
Gutsy question.
You're a shark.

07:14.608 --> 07:17.872
Sharks are winners,
and they don't look back,
'cause they don't have necks.

07:18.002 --> 07:21.440
Necks are for sheep.

07:21.571 --> 07:24.879
I am proud to be the shepherd
of this herd of sharks,

07:25.009 --> 07:29.579
and I am gonna lead you
to the top in this industry
of-- of--

07:29.709 --> 07:31.973
[ Whispers ]
Package delivery.Package delivery?

07:32.103 --> 07:35.367
Oh, God!
Fantastic!

07:35.497 --> 07:37.543
Now, the first order
of business...

07:37.673 --> 07:40.024
is to blame everything
on the guy before me.

07:40.154 --> 07:43.898
Professor?I'll ruin you
like I ruined this company!

07:44.028 --> 07:46.204
Terrific.
Question number one--

07:46.334 --> 07:48.206
What was
your overall business plan?

07:48.336 --> 07:52.209
[ Stammering ]
Business plan, uh, yes.

07:52.341 --> 07:54.995
I keep it here,
right next to my heart.

07:59.043 --> 08:02.045
This isn't a business plan.
It's an escape plan.

08:02.177 --> 08:05.572
So long, suckers!

08:05.701 --> 08:07.704
[ Giggling ]

08:07.834 --> 08:10.663
Fry, as a fellow
'80s dollar jockey,

08:10.793 --> 08:14.189
I'm makin' you
my new vice chairman.Wahoo!

08:14.319 --> 08:16.582
I'm rollin' up
the corporate ramp!
[ Chortles ]

08:16.713 --> 08:18.932
[ Zoidberg ]
It's the end of the line.We're ruined!

08:19.062 --> 08:23.850
What fevered dream
is this that bids to tear
this company in twain?

08:26.636 --> 08:29.682
[ Gravelly Voice ]
Thank you. Come again.

08:29.812 --> 08:32.250
That's what I call
a hostile makeover.

08:32.380 --> 08:36.515
- Hair gel?
- No, thanks. I make my own.
[ Grease Squishing ]

08:43.000 --> 08:46.177
- [ Signal Twitters, Dings ]
- [ Pedestrians Whirring ]

08:48.962 --> 08:51.399
This company's
gonna shoot
straight to the top...

08:51.530 --> 08:53.620
and stay there,
like Cyndi Lauper.

08:53.750 --> 08:58.538
I ask you, who is the number one
delivery service on Earth?

08:58.668 --> 09:01.671
- Is it
Planet Express, master?
- [ Laughs ]

09:01.802 --> 09:03.803
Is this guy
a shark or what?

09:03.933 --> 09:05.806
Seriously, though,
we stink out loud.

09:05.936 --> 09:08.330
Here's
the big Enchirito--

09:09.765 --> 09:12.115
Mom's Friendly Delivery Company.

09:12.246 --> 09:15.772
We can't compete with Mom!
Her company is big and evil.

09:15.903 --> 09:19.471
- Ours is small and neutral.
- Switzerland
is small and neutral.

09:19.601 --> 09:23.039
We're more like Germany--
ambitious and misunderstood.

09:23.171 --> 09:25.782
Look, everyone wants
to be like Germany.

09:25.913 --> 09:28.350
But do we really have
the pure strength of will?

09:28.480 --> 09:30.351
I say we do!

09:30.481 --> 09:32.919
Now, are we gonna let ourselves
get beaten by an old lady?

09:33.049 --> 09:36.009
- Yes, my liege.
- No, we're not!

09:36.139 --> 09:38.838
And as vice chairman,
I believe I speak
for the entire board...

09:38.969 --> 09:40.884
when I issue
this challenge to Mom!

09:41.014 --> 09:44.713
[ Zipper Unzipping ]
Look at my butt! Whooooo!
[ Glass Squeaking ]

09:44.845 --> 09:48.761
Whooo, whoo, whoo, whoo!You call that
a pressed ham?

09:48.892 --> 09:51.154
Walt,
hit the retaliate button! [ Razzing Continues ]

09:51.286 --> 09:53.592
[ Hemming, Hawing ]
Oh, let's see.

09:53.722 --> 09:56.378
Any button!
They all retaliate!

09:56.508 --> 09:59.947
- [ Panel Twittering ]
- [ Arm Whirring ]

10:02.950 --> 10:05.952
[ All Screaming ]

10:09.913 --> 10:13.787
- [ Cheering ]
- [ Bell Rings ]

10:13.917 --> 10:15.615
[ Both Grunting ]

10:15.745 --> 10:18.748
[ Growling ][ Howling ]

10:18.879 --> 10:21.316
Whoo! Yeah!
Hit 'em, hit 'em,
hit 'em!

10:21.446 --> 10:23.360
[ Laughs ]
Now, this is
the high life,

10:23.491 --> 10:25.668
watching apes
mangle each other
near celebrities.

10:25.798 --> 10:28.322
In my day,
we went to coke parties,
but the principle's the same.

10:28.452 --> 10:31.500
[ Ape Grunting ]

10:31.630 --> 10:34.764
Get your stinkin' trike off me,
you damn, dirty ape!

10:34.894 --> 10:37.636
Listen, big guy.
Now that you're my protégé,

10:37.767 --> 10:40.378
it's time I cut you in on
the secret to success.

10:40.509 --> 10:43.817
Any guesses?Uh, work
really, really hard?

10:43.947 --> 10:45.818
No.Oh, thank God!

10:45.948 --> 10:48.822
It's all about appearances.

10:48.951 --> 10:51.868
That's why it's time
to update our company's
stodgy image...

10:51.999 --> 10:54.392
and give it the sleek,
dazzling veneer...

10:54.523 --> 10:56.698
of the 1980s!

10:58.527 --> 11:02.443
[ Snoring ]

11:03.532 --> 11:05.447
[ Startled Gasps ]

11:05.576 --> 11:09.102
This company's on
the fast track to the "It List."
Blast fax kudos all around!

11:09.232 --> 11:13.193
Uh, hello?
We haven't made one delivery
since you two took over.

11:13.323 --> 11:16.893
Delivery has nothing to do
with the delivery business.

11:17.024 --> 11:19.895
Image, people! Image!
Scope out this new ad!

11:20.027 --> 11:24.205
[ Echoing ]
We are all one,
with one mind,

11:24.335 --> 11:26.206
one purpose, one pact.

11:26.336 --> 11:28.948
Our enemy shall be eaten
by scorpions.

11:29.078 --> 11:33.779
- And we shall bow down
and worship to ourselves.
- [ Yells ]

11:33.909 --> 11:36.783
We shall prevail!

11:38.914 --> 11:42.048
Hey, we were watching that!

11:43.876 --> 11:46.618
That was terrible!
People won't even know
what we do.

11:46.749 --> 11:49.883
I don't even know what we do.
Nah, just kiddin'.
[ Chuckles ]

11:50.013 --> 11:51.798
What are we,
like a bus or somethin'?

11:51.927 --> 11:54.148
Did you approve
that awful ad, Fry?

11:54.278 --> 11:56.716
Yes, I did, Leels,
and I'll tell you why.

11:56.846 --> 11:58.847
Because it grows
the brand.

11:58.979 --> 12:01.154
- Oh, Lord.
- [ Growls ]

12:01.284 --> 12:03.897
This company's circling
the drain, I tell you!

12:04.027 --> 12:07.291
- I'd sell my stock right now
for a sandwich.
- Sold!

12:10.424 --> 12:12.383
A complete sandwich?

12:12.514 --> 12:15.211
[ Laughs ]
You got fleeced.

12:15.342 --> 12:19.739
I would have settled for
a hard roll with ketchup inside.
[ Slurping ]

12:22.306 --> 12:25.875
What is this moose drip?

12:27.398 --> 12:29.486
"The New Delivery Kings?"

12:29.618 --> 12:32.663
I'm sick of hearing about
those turtle squirts.

12:32.794 --> 12:35.667
But they're kings, Mommy.Jam a bastard in it,
you crap!

12:35.798 --> 12:37.668
[ All ]
Ow!

12:40.280 --> 12:42.717
Enjoy our private
dining room, folks.

12:42.849 --> 12:44.764
This is where we serve
our richest,

12:44.894 --> 12:47.941
most successful chumps.Tonight,
that's us.

12:48.071 --> 12:50.421
What have you got
that's really overpriced?Everything.

12:50.552 --> 12:53.903
Bring me that.Make it two. And a glass
of all your water.

12:54.033 --> 12:57.080
Okay, let's work on
your execu-speak.

12:57.211 --> 13:01.780
I'm worried about "blank."Don't you worry about "blank."
Let me worry about "blank."

13:01.910 --> 13:03.783
Good.
I also would have accepted,

13:03.913 --> 13:07.481
"Blank? Blank?You're not
looking at the big picture!"

13:07.611 --> 13:09.962
[ Clearing Throat ]

13:10.092 --> 13:12.095
[ Gasps ]
What a pleasant surprise.

13:12.225 --> 13:16.360
Shut up, booger blaster!
It's time the three of us
had a talk.

13:16.490 --> 13:18.754
I'll handle this, Fry.
You get back to the farm,

13:18.884 --> 13:21.538
shift some paradigms,
revolutionize outside the box.

13:21.669 --> 13:25.107
I'm on it.
But if you need me,
you know where I'll be.

13:25.239 --> 13:27.544
[ Screaming ]

13:27.676 --> 13:29.721
[ Grunting, Groaning ]
Okay.

13:31.811 --> 13:35.118
Call me a booger blaster.
I'll blast a booger
so hard that--

13:35.249 --> 13:37.860
Fry, we're worried
about Planet Express.

13:37.990 --> 13:41.471
Don't you worry
about Planet Express.
Let me worry about "blank."

13:41.602 --> 13:43.996
That guy is nothin'
but a flashy con man,

13:44.126 --> 13:46.782
and you've been hypnotized
by his swingin' baloney.

13:46.913 --> 13:49.784
- You've changed, Fry.
- What? I haven't changed.

13:49.915 --> 13:51.787
[ Intercom Twitters ]Suz, have I changed?

13:51.918 --> 13:54.702
No, sir, Mister Fry.Thanks, doll.

13:54.834 --> 13:57.400
I don't care what
Ms. Johnson says.

13:57.532 --> 14:00.708
That Guy's turning this place
into some kind of "business."

14:00.840 --> 14:05.148
This isn't a business.
I've always thought of it more
as a source of cheap labor.

14:05.278 --> 14:08.586
Like a family.You're right,
Professor.

14:08.716 --> 14:11.937
We may not be
a traditional family like
the Murphys next door...

14:12.067 --> 14:14.854
or the lesbian coven
across the street,
but we are a family.

14:14.984 --> 14:17.986
And That Guy
understands that.

14:18.118 --> 14:20.076
Everyone's fired,
and we're out of business.

14:20.206 --> 14:21.860
[ Collective Gasp ][ Amy ]
Oh, no!

14:21.990 --> 14:23.993
I'm gonna sell
Planet Express to Mom,

14:24.124 --> 14:27.431
so she can gut the company
and eliminate us as competitors.

14:27.562 --> 14:30.043
Don't let the door
hit you on the way out,

14:30.173 --> 14:33.001
'cause I don't want
ass prints on my new door!

14:42.881 --> 14:46.841
Uh, Ms. Johnson?
Please bring in
some more chair fuel.

14:51.846 --> 14:54.023
I had no idea
the company would be sold!

14:54.153 --> 14:57.113
I was just an innocent suck-up!
You've got to believe me!

14:57.244 --> 15:00.464
Just leave us alone, and let us
clear out our lockers.

15:00.595 --> 15:04.033
Yeah!
[ Chuckles ]

15:04.163 --> 15:06.687
[ Sobbing ]
It's so sad.

15:06.817 --> 15:10.909
Where will I go?
What will I do?

15:11.039 --> 15:13.650
You have Mrs. Darlinghaven's
cotillion at 7:00, ma'am.

15:13.782 --> 15:16.567
[ Sobbing ]
Oh, that'll be fun.

15:19.048 --> 15:21.136
[ Sighs ]

15:21.268 --> 15:23.618
Ms. Johnson,
you've never lied to me.

15:23.748 --> 15:26.447
- Am I still a good person?
- I don't know, sir.

15:26.576 --> 15:28.666
I'm a program
built into the intercom.

15:28.797 --> 15:30.929
I've got to redeem myself.

15:31.059 --> 15:33.671
Somehow, some time,
for some reason,

15:33.802 --> 15:36.152
I'll block this takeover!

15:36.283 --> 15:38.937
Mr. Fry,
your 2:00 magician is here.

15:39.067 --> 15:42.158
Believe it or not,
I have more important
things to do today...

15:42.288 --> 15:44.246
than laugh
and clap my hands.

15:44.378 --> 15:46.249
Reschedule.

16:07.879 --> 16:11.230
[ Traders Chattering ]

16:11.360 --> 16:14.625
- [ Clacking ]
- Sell 100 soylent beans!

16:14.755 --> 16:18.193
- Buy 3,000 corn bellies!
- Two hundred cans Whoop-Ass!

16:18.325 --> 16:21.631
Three big bags of trash! [ Man ]
Attention, please.

16:21.763 --> 16:24.984
The takeover of PlanEx Corp
by Mom's Delivery Company...

16:25.114 --> 16:27.855
will take place
in the business center
in ten minutes.

16:27.986 --> 16:31.337
[ Bellows ]
I am Jorell,
Master of Scheduling!

16:38.301 --> 16:42.000
Okay.
We got the hot tub hot,
the wine coolers cool.

16:42.130 --> 16:45.047
- It's "Hammer" time!
- [ Booing ]

16:45.177 --> 16:47.048
You suck!

16:49.355 --> 16:53.750
According to regulations,
both companies must approve
the takeover.

16:53.881 --> 16:56.667
Planet Express shareholders,
cast your votes.

16:56.798 --> 17:01.542
Great banda of Uganda!
We can vote against it![ Laughing ]

17:01.672 --> 17:04.458
I'll vote it down like a raise
for schoolteachers!

17:13.815 --> 17:17.123
- [ Bender ] What the--
- [ Gasping ]

17:17.252 --> 17:19.080
I neglected to mention
that the shares...

17:19.211 --> 17:22.519
I bought from Dr. Zoidberg
gave me majority control.

17:22.650 --> 17:25.826
Zoidberg owned 51 percent
of the company?

17:25.957 --> 17:29.178
The shares were worthless,
and he kept askin'
for toilet paper!

17:29.308 --> 17:33.616
And now,
if MomCorp shareholders
will cast theirballots.

17:42.017 --> 17:43.932
Um, uhh.

17:44.063 --> 17:46.500
[ Twitters ] [ Buzzer Buzzing ]

17:46.630 --> 17:49.633
Uhh!
The ballot was confusing!

17:49.763 --> 17:52.983
- How about a hand recount?
- Okay. Ow!

17:53.115 --> 17:56.291
The takeover
of Planet Express is approved!

17:56.423 --> 17:57.554
[ Booing ]Ah, man!

17:57.684 --> 18:00.078
This stinks!Madam is outraged!

18:00.209 --> 18:03.517
Security! I want that bunch
of rowdies out of here!

18:05.039 --> 18:08.260
[ Commotion ]

18:08.391 --> 18:12.090
[ Snoring ]

18:12.221 --> 18:16.398
MomCorp will now purchase
all outstanding shares
of Planet Express...

18:16.529 --> 18:19.097
at the current market price,
which is--

18:19.228 --> 18:21.099
[ Screen Beeps ]
107!

18:21.230 --> 18:23.405
[ Grunting ]

18:23.537 --> 18:25.407
Whoa! Ow!

18:25.538 --> 18:27.671
And also,
it hurt my feelings!

18:27.801 --> 18:30.065
What are you solids
griping about?

18:30.195 --> 18:33.286
Your shares are worth
$107 apiece.

18:33.415 --> 18:36.288
They are? Oh, my God!
I'm a millionaire!

18:36.419 --> 18:38.855
Suddenly, I have an opinion
about the capital gains tax!

18:38.987 --> 18:40.857
Yeah!
All right!I'm even richer!

18:40.989 --> 18:43.817
[ Groans ]
I have no shares!

18:43.948 --> 18:47.473
[ Sobs ]
Wait! My sandwich!

18:47.604 --> 18:50.128
Has it also appreciated
in value?
Please, oh, please!

18:50.259 --> 18:53.000
You didn't even refrigerate it,
you spineless lobster!

18:53.132 --> 18:56.003
You had to drag
spines into this!

18:56.134 --> 18:58.093
[ Sobs ]

18:59.224 --> 19:01.791
[ Clears Throat ]

19:01.923 --> 19:04.185
As vice chairman
of Planet Express,
I'd like to say a few words.

19:04.317 --> 19:08.364
There comes a time
for every man who becomes rich
and deserts his friends,

19:08.494 --> 19:10.365
when he goes back
how it was.

19:10.497 --> 19:12.193
For me, that time is now.

19:12.325 --> 19:16.111
So I ask you, as a friend--
Won't you stop this deal?

19:16.241 --> 19:19.288
Fry, I'm an '80s guy.
Friendship to me means
that for two bucks...

19:19.419 --> 19:22.290
I beat you with a pool cue
till you got detached retinas.

19:22.422 --> 19:24.336
The deal will go ahead as--

19:24.467 --> 19:27.165
[ Pained Cry,
Squishing Sounds ]

19:29.690 --> 19:33.084
[ Squishing Continues ]

19:33.214 --> 19:35.391
- My bones!
- [ Gasps ]

19:35.521 --> 19:37.175
Oh, my God!
His bone-itis!

19:37.306 --> 19:41.267
I was so busy bein' an '80s guy,
I forgot to cure it!

19:41.396 --> 19:44.226
[ Bones Cracking ]

19:47.316 --> 19:52.451
My only regret is...
that I have... bone-itis.

19:52.582 --> 19:55.628
[ Cracking, Squishing ]He's dead!

19:55.759 --> 19:58.197
[ Gasping, Murmuring ]

19:58.326 --> 20:00.415
Pry out his fillings,
feed him to the jackals,

20:00.547 --> 20:02.679
and let's get on
with the sale!I don't think so.

20:02.809 --> 20:07.336
Because as vice chairman
of the company, I gain
voting control of his shares.

20:07.467 --> 20:11.122
- Don't be a fool, you idiot!
- I'll be whatever I want to do!

20:11.252 --> 20:14.386
That Guy was
the greatest businessman
that ever lived.

20:14.517 --> 20:17.432
And before his mysterious death,
he taught me everything he knew.

20:17.564 --> 20:19.695
[ Sign Twitters ]But some things
I had to learn myself.

20:19.826 --> 20:22.351
[ Twittering ]I learned
that money is fine,

20:22.481 --> 20:24.570
but in the end,
what counts is people.[ Twittering Continues ]

20:24.701 --> 20:27.574
People you love.
You can't put a price on that.

20:27.703 --> 20:29.923
And so I'm giving up
control of the company...

20:30.054 --> 20:31.925
to a man of enormous
experience,

20:32.056 --> 20:34.363
Professor
Hubert Farnsworth.

20:34.493 --> 20:36.799
[ Snoring ]
O-Oh, you! Wh-What?

20:36.931 --> 20:40.368
I'm awake!
I'm awake!

20:40.500 --> 20:45.374
- [ Digits Clanking ]
- Fry! Stop doin'
the right thing, you jerk!

20:45.505 --> 20:49.029
Let Mom buy the company!
We all want to be filthy,
stinking rich!

20:49.160 --> 20:51.162
Trust me.
Two out of three
doesn't cut it.

20:51.292 --> 20:54.296
You mean,
you'd rather be rich
than work together?

20:54.426 --> 20:57.691
- Hell yeah!
- In my whole life,

20:57.820 --> 21:00.824
this company was
the only place I ever
really felt at home.

21:00.954 --> 21:03.696
But if being millionaires
is more important
to you than our--

21:03.826 --> 21:08.005
It is!friendship, then I'll sell
Planet Express... for you.

21:09.397 --> 21:11.704
Millionaires,
nothing!

21:11.835 --> 21:14.142
The stock's only worth
three kajiggers!

21:14.272 --> 21:15.796
Ah, come on!Dagnabbit!
[ Groaning ]

21:15.925 --> 21:19.278
My Jah! It's worth less now
than when it was worthless!

21:19.407 --> 21:21.540
It is? Yahoo!

21:21.671 --> 21:24.369
We're poor
no matter what I do!
The deal is off!

21:24.500 --> 21:27.286
- [ Beeps ]
- [ Twittering, Ringing ]

21:27.415 --> 21:31.463
Ah-ha! Once again,
the conservative
sandwich-heavy portfolio...

21:31.594 --> 21:33.422
pays off
for the hungry investor!

21:33.552 --> 21:36.163
[ Slurps, Gulps ]

21:36.295 --> 21:39.340
Oh, I'm ruined!
[ Sobs ]

21:39.471 --> 21:41.951
Why? Why?

21:42.083 --> 21:45.346
Look, so we're not millionaires.
At least we all still get
to work together.

21:45.478 --> 21:49.220
[ All Grumbling ]Shut your fat mouth.

21:49.351 --> 21:52.222
See you guys Monday!
